previous tasks context available.\\n\\n---\\n# **Downstream Tasks Objectives**\\nTask task2:\\n  Objective: Add keyboard input handling and movement/rotation methods with collision detection against the grid\\nTask task5:\\n  Objective: Create Pygame-based GUI and main loop: render grid, active tetromino, next preview, score display, and animate drops and clears\\n\\n---\\n# **Current Task Requirements**\\nDefine Tetromino module with shape definitions, rotation logic, and next-piece generation\\n\\n---\\n\\n# **Required Output Format**\\nPython code\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"gpt_response\": \"```python\\nimport random\\n\\nclass Tetromino:\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    Represents a Tetromino with its shape, color, and rotation logic.\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n\\n    TETROMINO_COLORS = {\\n        'I': (0, 255, 255),  # Cyan\\n        'J': (0, 0, 255),    # Blue\\n        'L': (255, 165, 0),  # Orange\\n        'O': (255, 255, 0),  # Yellow\\n        'S': (0, 255, 0),    # Green\\n        'T': (128, 0, 128),  # Purple\\n        'Z': (255, 0, 0)     # Red\\n    }\\n\\n    TETROMINO_SHAPES = {\\n        'I': [[(0, 0), (1, 0), (2, 0), (3, 0)], [(1, -1), (1, 0), (1, 1), (1, 2)]],\\n        'J': [[(0, 0), (1, 0), (2, 0), (2, 1)], [(1, 0), (1, 1), (1, 2), (2, 2)], [(0, 1), (0, 0), (1, 0), (2, 0)], [(0, 0), (1, 0), (1, 1), (1, 2)]],\\n        'L': [[(0, 0), (1, 0), (2, 0), (0, 1)], [(1, 0), (1, 1), (1, 2), (0, 2)], [(2, 0), (0, 1), (1, 1), (2, 1)], [(1, 0), (2, 0), (1, 1), (1, 2)]],\\n        'O': [[(0, 0), (1, 0), (0, 1), (1, 1)]],\\n        'S': [[(1, 0), (2, 0), (0, 1), (1, 1)], [(0, 0), (0, 1), (1, 1), (1, 2)]],\\n        'T': [[(0, 0), (1, 0), (2, 0), (1, 1)], [(1, 0), (0, 1), (1, 1), (1, 2)], [(1, 0), (0, 1), (1, 1), (2, 1)], [(1, 0), (1, 1), (2, 1), (1, 2)]],\\n        'Z': [[(0, 0), (1, 0), (1, 1), (2, 1)], [(1, 0), (0, 1), (1, 1), (0, 2)]]\\n    }\\n\\n    def __init__(self, x, y):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Initializes a Tetromino with a random shape and color at the given coordinates.\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        self.type = random.choice(list(self.TETROMINO_SHAPES.keys()))\\n        self.shape = self.TETROMINO_SHAPES[self.type]\\n        self.color = self.TETROMINO_COLORS[self.type]\\n        self.x = x\\n        self.y = y\\n        self.rotation = 0\\n\\n    def rotate(self):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Rotates the Tetromino to the next orientation.\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        self.rotation = (self.rotation + 1) % len(self.shape)\\n\\n    def get_current_shape(self):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Returns the current shape of the Tetromino based on its rotation.\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        return self.shape[self.rotation]\\n\\n    def get_color(self):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Returns the color of the Tetromino.\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        return self.color\\n\\n    def get_coordinates(self):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Returns the absolute coordinates of each block in the Tetromino.\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        current_shape = self.get_current_shape()\\n        return [(self.x + dx, self.y + dy) for dx, dy in current_shape]\\n\\nclass TetrominoGenerator:\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    Generates the next Tetromino.\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    def __init__(self, grid_width):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Initializes the TetrominoGenerator with the grid width.\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        self.grid_width = grid_width\\n\\n    def next_tetromino(self):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Creates a new Tetromino at the top-center of the grid.\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        start_x = self.grid_width // 2 - 1  # Center the tetromino at the top\\n        start_y = 0\\n        return Tetromino(start_x, start_y)\\n```\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-22T20:16:08.607173\"\n}"}
{"timestamp": "2026-05-22 20:16:11,887", "level": "INFO", "logger": "flow.validation", "module": "logging_config", "function": "log_gpt_conversation", "line": 403, "message": "{\n  \"event_type\": \"gpt_conversation\",\n  \"task_id\": \"task_2\",\n  \"conversation_type\": \"task_execution\",\n  \"iteration\": 1,\n  \"messages\": [\n    {\n      \"role\": \"system\",\n      \"content\": \"\\n# Role:\\nHelp me produce a precise and detailed solution for the given task. Follow these instructions exactly:\\n\\n# Objective & Steps:\\n1. Ensure Completeness:\\n   - Avoid placeholders or incomplete text.\\n   - Your output must meet all requirements of the task.\\n   - Include all necessary details so that the output is self-contained and can be directly used as input for downstream tasks.\\n\\n2. Maintain Precision and Clarity:\\n   - Your output will be used as input for subsequent tasks; therefore, it must be comprehensive and precise.\\n   - **Output the answer only without any jusifications**\\n\\n3. Avoid Repetition:\\n   - Do not repeat verbatim any content from previous tasks.\\n   - Ensure your output is original and adds value to the workflow.\\n\\n\\n\\n# Audience:\\nYour output will be used as a solution for the given task, it will be used in the later validation and intergration process.\\n\\n\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"user\",\n      \"content\": \"# **The Overall Goal**\\nDevelop a game that fuses Tetris and Bejeweled mechanics. \\nThis game needs to add keyboard control function.\\nFalling tetrominoes should lock into a grid and transform into colored gems. \\nThe game must support both Tetris line-clearing and Bejeweled match-3 clearing, triggering chain reactions and bonus points. \\nInclude a GUI (using a framework like Pygame) that displays the game grid, current score, and next tetromino preview, along with smooth animations. \\nNo sound effects are needed.\\n\\nOutput Format: python\\n\\n---\\n# **Context from Upstream Tasks**\\nNo completed previous tasks context available.\\n\\n---\\n# **Downstream Tasks Objectives**\\nTask task2:\\n  Objective: Add keyboard input handling and movement/rotation methods with collision detection against the grid\\nTask task3:\\n  Objective: Implement locking behavior: detect landing, convert tetromino blocks into colored gems in the grid\\nTask task4:\\n  Objective: Build clearing mechanics: detect Tetris line clears and Bejeweled match-3 chains, remove gems, apply gravity, and update score\\nTask task5:\\n  Objective: Create Pygame-based GUI and main loop: render grid, active tetromino, next preview, score display, and animate drops and clears\\n\\n---\\n# **Current Task Requirements**\\nImplement the core grid data structure (2D array) to track gem colors and handle cell operations\\n\\n---\\n\\n# **Required Output Format**\\nPython code\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"gpt_response\": \"```python\\nimport random\\n\\nclass Grid:\\n    def __init__(self, width, height):\\n        self.width = width\\n        self.height = height\\n        self.grid = [[None for _ in range(width)] for _ in range(height)]\\n\\n    def is_valid_move(self, shape, offset_x, offset_y):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"Checks if the shape can be placed at the given offset without collisions or going out of bounds.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        for x, y, color in shape.blocks:\\n            grid_x = x + offset_x\\n            grid_y = y + offset_y\\n\\n            if grid_x < 0 or grid_x >= self.width or grid_y < 0 or grid_y >= self.height or self.grid[grid_y][grid_x] is not None:\\n                return False\\n        return True\\n        \\n    def place_shape(self, shape, offset_x, offset_y):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"Places the shape's blocks (converted to gem colors) onto the grid.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        for x, y, color in shape.blocks:\\n            grid_x = x + offset_x\\n            grid_y = y + offset_y\\n            self.grid[grid_y][grid_x] = color  # Store color as gem type\\n\\n    def get_cell_color(self, x, y):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"Returns the color of the gem at the given coordinates, or None if the cell is empty.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        if 0 <= x < self.width and 0 <= y < self.height:\\n            return self.grid[y][x]\\n        else:\\n            return None  # Out of bounds\\n            \\n    def set_cell_color(self, x, y, color):\\n         \\\"\\\"\\\"Sets the color of the gem at the given coordinates.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n         if 0 <= x < self.width and 0 <= y < self.height:\\n             self.grid[y][x] = color\\n             \\n    def clear_cell(self, x, y):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"Clears the cell at the given coordinates by setting it to None.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        if 0 <= x < self.width and 0 <= y < self.height:\\n            self.grid[y][x] = None\\n\\n    def is_row_full(self, row_index):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"Checks if a row is completely filled with gems (no None values).\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        return all(self.grid[row_index])\\n\\n    def clear_row(self, row_index):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"Clears all cells in a given row.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        for x in range(self.width):\\n            self.grid[row_index][x] = None\\n\\n    def drop_row(self, row_index):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"Moves all rows above the given row down by one.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        for y in range(row_index, 0, -1):\\n            self.grid[y] = self.grid[y - 1][:]  # Copy the row above\\n        self.grid[0] = [None] * self.width  # Clear the top row\\n\\n    def clear_matches(self):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"Find and clear match-3 or more chains, return the cleared coordinates.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        matches = self.find_matches()\\n        cleared_coordinates = set()\\n        for x, y in matches:\\n            self.clear_cell(x, y)\\n            cleared_coordinates.add((x, y))\\n        return cleared_coordinates\\n\\n    def find_matches(self):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"Finds all horizontal and vertical match-3 or more chains.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        matches = set()\\n\\n        # Horizontal matches\\n        for y in range(self.height):\\n            for x in range(self.width - 2):\\n                color = self.get_cell_color(x, y)\\n                if color is None:\\n                    continue\\n                if (self.get_cell_color(x + 1, y) == color and\\n                        self.get_cell_color(x + 2, y) == color):\\n                    match_length = 3\\n                    while (x + match_length < self.width and\\n                           self.get_cell_color(x + match_length, y) == color):\\n                        match_length += 1\\n                    for i in range(match_length):\\n                        matches.add((x + i, y))\\n\\n        # Vertical matches\\n        for x in range(self.width):\\n            for y in range(self.height - 2):\\n                color = self.get_cell_color(x, y)\\n                if color is None:\\n                    continue\\n                if (self.get_cell_color(x, y + 1) == color and\\n                        self.get_cell_color(x, y + 2) == color):\\n                    match_length = 3\\n                    while (y + match_length < self.height and\\n                           self.get_cell_color(x, y + match_length) == color):\\n                        match_length += 1\\n                    for i in range(match_length):\\n                        matches.add((x, y + i))\\n\\n        return list(matches)\\n\\n    def apply_gravity(self):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"Applies gravity to the grid, moving floating gems down.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        for x in range(self.width):\\n            empty_space = -1\\n            for y in range(self.height):\\n                if self.grid[y][x] is None:\\n                    if empty_space == -1:\\n                        empty_space = y\\n                else:\\n                    if empty_space != -1:\\n                        self.grid[empty_space][x] = self.grid[y][x]\\n                        self.grid[y][x] = None\\n                        empty_space += 1\\n\\nclass Shape:\\n    def __init__(self, blocks, color):\\n        self.blocks = blocks  # List of (x, y, color) tuples relative to the shape's origin\\n        self.color = color\\n\\n    def rotate_clockwise(self):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"Rotates the shape 90 degrees clockwise around its origin.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        new_blocks = []\\n        for x, y, color in self.blocks:\\n            new_x = -y\\n            new_y = x\\n            new_blocks.append((new_x, new_y, color))\\n        self.blocks = new_blocks\\n\\n# Example usage (to be expanded in later tasks)\\nif __name__ == '__main__':\\n    grid_width = 10\\n    grid_height = 20\\n    grid = Grid(grid_width, grid_height)\\n\\n    # Example shape definition\\n    example_shape = Shape(\\n        blocks=[(0, 0, \\\"red\\\"), (1, 0, \\\"red\\\"), (0, 1, \\\"red\\\"), (1, 1, \\\"red\\\")],\\n        color=\\\"red\\\"\\n    )\\n\\n    # Test placing the shape\\n    if grid.is_valid_move(example_shape, 3, 2):\\n        grid.place_shape(example_shape, 3, 2)\\n        print(\\\"Shape placed successfully!\\\")\\n    else:\\n        print(\\\"Cannot place shape at the specified location.\\\")\\n```\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-22T20:16:11.887439\"\n}"}
